n\nThe Chinese Communist 18th Air Division at Canton in South China has been strengthened by the addition of 28 MIG-15's and now has 82 planes.\n\nApparently to absorb the increase, a third regiment of the division has been activated for the first time. Two of the division's regiments, with a total of 54 planes, are operating from Paiyun airfield at Canton. The third, with 28 aircraft, is flying from the recently completed field at Foshan, about 20 miles southwest of Canton.\n\nComment: An increase of jet fighter strength raises the estimated jet fighter strength in Central-South China to about 190. Combat-trained in Korea, the 18th Division is the only known jet fighter unit based along China's southern coast", "token_count": 126, "token_end_0based": 227, "token_start_0based": 102, "token_text": "3 chinese communist mig division at canton strengthened the chinese communist 18th air division at canton in south china has been strengthened by the addition of 28 mig-15's and now has 82 planes apparently to absorb the increase a third regiment of the division has been activated for the first time two of the division's regiments with a total of 54 planes are operating from paiyun airfield at canton the third with 28 aircraft is flying from the recently completed field at foshan about 20 miles southwest of canton comment an increase of jet fighter strength raises the estimated jet fighter strength in central-south china to about 190 combat-trained in korea the 18th division is the only known jet fighter unit based along china's southern coast", "unred_source_page": 5}
